items.title: Google Cloud updates its AI Agent Builder with new observability dashboard and faster build-and-deploy tools
items.summary: Google Cloud has introduced a big update in a bid to keep AI developers on its Vertex AI platform for concepting, designing, building, testing, deploying and modifying AI agents in enterprise use cases . The new features include additional governance tools for enterprises and expanding the capabilities for creating agents with just a few lines of code . Google’s no-code platform for enterprises to create agents and connect these to orchestration frameworks like LangChain .

items.title: Magentic Marketplace: an open-source simulation environment for studying agentic markets
items.summary: Magentic Marketplace is an open-source simulation environment for studying agentic market designs . The tool is designed to explore what can happen when AI agents interact and transact at scale . Microsoft Research is working with Microsoft to develop the tool to use in the future of AI agents to create digital marketplaces . It is based on the work of Microsoft Research, published by Microsoft Research .

items.title: From logs to insights: The AI breakthrough redefining observability
items.summary: Elastic's Streams aims to become the primary signal for investigations by taking noisy logs and turning them into patterns, context and meaning . Streams uses AI to automatically partition and parse raw logs to extract relevant fields, and greatly reduce the effort required of SREs to make logs usable . A Kubernetes cluster alone can emit 30 to 50 gigabytes of logs a day .

items.title: AI’s capacity crunch: Latency risk, escalating costs, and the coming surge-pricing breakpoint
items.summary: Val Bercovici, chief AI officer at WEKA, spoke at VentureBeat’s AI Impact stop in NYC . He says AI is headed toward the same economic reckoning — especially for inference — when the focus turns to profitability . L latency, cloud lock-in, and runaway costs are pushing AI toward its own version of surge pricing .

items.title: Databricks research reveals that building better AI judges isn't just a technical concern, it's a people problem
items.summary: Databricks' Judge Builder is a framework for creating judges for AI evaluation . It was first deployed as part of the company's Agent Bricks technology earlier this year . The intelligence of AI models isn't blocking enterprise deployments, it's the inability to define and measure quality in the first place . Judge Builder creates highly specific evaluation criteria tailored to each organization's domain expertise and business requirements .

items.title: Attention ISN'T all you need?! New Qwen3 variant Brumby-14B-Base leverages Power Retention technique
items.summary: Every major large language model (LLM) has been built on some variation of its central mechanism: Attention . Attention is powerful, but it is also expensive — its computational and memory costs scale quadratically with context length . As models aim to reason across documents, codebases, or video streams lasting hours or days, attention becomes the architecture’s Achilles’ heel .

items.title: RedCodeAgent: Automatic red-teaming agent against diverse code agents
items.summary: Learn how RedCodeAgent automates and improves “red-teaming’s” attack simulations to help uncover real-world threats that other methods overlook . The post was published by Microsoft Research at Microsoft Research on Tuesday at 10:30 a.m. ET . items.title: 98% of market researchers use AI daily, but 4 in 10 say it makes errors — revealing a major trust problem
items.summary: 98% of U.S. market research and insights professionals now incorporate AI tools into their work . 72% of those surveyed use AI tools daily or more frequently, according to a new Harris Poll . The overwhelming majority — 89% — say AI has made their work better, with the improvement described as significant . But the same survey reveals deep unease about the technology's reliability problems .

items.title: Forget Fine-Tuning: SAP’s RPT-1 Brings Ready-to-Use AI for Business Tasks
items.summary: SAP has released its own "tabular" AI model, called SAP RPT-1, which is pre-trained with business and enterprise knowledge out of the box . The value of the new model lies in its ability to perform various enterprise tasks, such as predictive analytics . The model will be generally available in “Q4 of 2025” and be deployed via SAP’s AI Foundation .
